  "A submarine has a hull volume of 6500 m^3 and weighs 6.0 x 10^7 N. How much water must it take into ballast tanks to achieve neutral buoyancy in seawater (density 1025 kg/m^3)?": "",
  "About 5,250,000 kg": "",
